post_text:
Forsyth Elementary would like to honor our teachers and staff that go above –and-beyond-the-call-of-duty. We are implementing a recognition program called the “Starfish Award”. Our Starfish Award is based on The Starfish Story. Adapted from the book, The Star Thrower, by Loren Eiseley, this story can be found on the Web in many forms. The moral of the story is that anyone can make a difference in someone’s life; making a difference is important even if it only affects one other person. The goal of the program is to honor and recognize staff members who have made a difference by contributing a personal effort for the benefit of others and their community. Unique to this program is the nomination process. Staff members may be nominated by their colleagues, parents or community members based on above-and-beyond-the-call-of-duty behaviors that promote our school and its vision.

The 2nd quarter recipient of the Starfish Award is Mr. Mathis. Great Job Mr. Mathis, keep up the great work!

post_text: Kindergarten screening is scheduled for August 6 and August 7. Children must be five years of age on or before July 31 to enroll in kindergarten. To be eligible for screening parents must have Child's "State" birth certificate, social security number, up to date immunization record, and proof of residency. No child will be enrolled or allowed to attend the first day of the regular school year without prior screening. For more information, and to schedule an appointment, please call the elementary office at 546-6381. We look forward to meeting with you and your child!

There is a new website that has been launched to provide information to Missouri parents about public education and your student. It is called Moparent.com. There is no cost to subscribe and your email address will not be shared with advertisers or any other entity. The site includes timely information about activities you can do with your child or student, explanation of education issues, and tips that will help your student be successful in school.

By signing up on the website before December 1, you become eligible to win $500 for yourself and for your school. You will also receive periodic emails with more information and tips.
